doc.ContractDescription: THE FIRST STEP IN THIS PROCESS IS TO CONFIGURE THE ARC7 CODE PROPERLY TO SUIT OUR NEEDS. THE BIGGEST ADJUSTMENT THAT NEEDS TO HAPPEN IS ALONG THE INNER BOUNDARY. THE CODE WORKS BY FIXING THE LOWER BOUNDARY TEMPERATURE TO A USER SPECIFIED VALUE AND ADJUSTING THE DENSITY THERE THROUGH THE ASSUMPTION OF RADIATIVE ENERGY BALANCE. WE NEEDED TO MAKE THE LOWER BOUNDARY TEMPERATURE A FACTOR OF FIVE SMALLER THAN THE VALUE IT HAD BEEN IN PAST USES OF THE CODE AND THIS HAS REQUIRED US TO MAKE OTHER ADJUSTMENTS TO HOW THE ENERGY BALANCE IS HANDLED FOR THE DENSITY CALCULATION. ONCE WE HAVE A RELIABLE SET OF BOUNDARY VALUES AND CRITERIA IN PLACE, THE CODE SHOULD BE EQUIPPED TO SEE THE THERMAL INSTABILITIES. WHEN WE BEGIN TO SEE THE CONDENSATIONS, AN ANALYSIS OF THE SP PERIODICITY CAN BE PERFORMED. WE HAVE ALREADY WRITTEN CODE TO DO THIS TASK. WE CAN CHOOSE A FIXED POINT IN SPACE ALONG THE EQUATOR, SAY 15 SOLAR RADII FROM THE SOLAR CENTER, AND LOOK AT FLUCTUATIONS IN MASS DENSITY THROUGH TIME. AS WE ADJUST THE HEATING SCALING HEIGHT, WE WILL BE ABLE TO SEE THE CHANGES IN THE FREQUENCY OF THESE FLUCTUATIONS. THIS ANALYSIS WILL ALSO BE EXTREMELY USEFUL FOR COMPARING OUR WORK TO THE ACTUAL OBSERVATIONS SEEN BY VIALL AND VOURLIDAS 2015. THE RESULTS OF THE PROJECT WILL BE PUBLISHED IN PEER REVIEWED JOURNALS. WE ANTICIPATE THAT THREE PAPERS WILL RESULT FROM THIS WORK, THE FIRST DETAILING THE RELEVANT PHYSICS AND ITS IMPLEMENTATION WITHIN THE ARC7 CODE, THE SECOND DETAILING THE RESULTS OF A PARAMETER STUDY AND NOTING THE EFFECTS ON SP PRODUCTION RATES, AND THE THIRD PAPER COMPARING THE RESULTS OF THE PARAMETER STUDY TO OBSERVATIONS. WE WILL ALSO PRESENT THESE FINDINGS AT CONFERENCES. THE RESEARCH WILL BE CARRIED OUT BY DREXEL GRADUATE STUDENT MICHAEL SCHLENKER, WORKING UNDER THE LOCAL SUPERVISION OF PI STEPHEN MCMILLAN, IN CLOSE COLLABORATION WITH NASA INVESTIGATORS SPIRO ANTIOCHOS AND PETER MACNEICE AT GSFC. WHEN THE PROJECT CONCLUDES, THE CODE DEVELOPED FOR THESE STUDIES WILL BE TURNED OVER TO THE GSFC TEAM.
